= Linecook

A shell script generator.

== Description

Linecook generates shell scripts using an extensible set of ERB helpers. The
shell scripts and associated resources (files, subscripts, etc) make up
packages that can be used, for example, to provision servers.

The workflow is like this:

* define helpers
* write recipes using the helpers
* generate script packages from the recipes

Linecook provides a command-line tool for generating helpers, packages, and
for running a development vm using {VirtualBox}[http://www.virtualbox.org].
Helpers and recipes can be shared as gems; the canonical shell helpers are
available through {Linebook}[http://rubygems.org/gems/linebook/].

See the documentation for a thorough {Tutorial}[link:files/Tutorial/0%20-%20Intro.html].

== Usage

Generate a cookbook.

  % linecook init chalkboard
  % cd chalkboard

Make a helper.

  [helpers/chalkboard/echo_in_color.erb]
  Echo a string in color.
  (color, str)
    color_codes = Hash[*%W{
      black       0;30   red         0;31
      white       1;37   green       0;32
      light_gray  0;37   blue        0;34
    }]
  --
  echo -e '\033[<%= color_codes[color.to_s] %>m<%= str %>\033[0m'

Define default attributes.

  [attributes/chalkboard.rb]
  attrs['chalkboard']['n'] = 3
  attrs['chalkboard']['color'] = 'white'
  attrs['chalkboard']['message'] = 'I will not manually configure my server'

Use both in a recipe.

  [recipes/chalkboard.rb]
  helpers "chalkboard"
  attributes "chalkboard"
  
  attrs['chalkboard']['n'].times do
    echo_in_color attrs['chalkboard']['color'], attrs['chalkboard']['message']
  end

Define a package to use the recipe; set non-default attributes as needed.

  [packages/chalkboard.yml]
  chalkboard:
    n: 5
    color: blue

Generate the package from the helpers, attributes, and recipe.

  % linecook build

Check the package directory to inspect the resulting script.

  % cat packages/chalkboard/run
  echo -e '\033[0;34mI will not manually configure my server\033[0m'
  echo -e '\033[0;34mI will not manually configure my server\033[0m'
  echo -e '\033[0;34mI will not manually configure my server\033[0m'
  echo -e '\033[0;34mI will not manually configure my server\033[0m'
  echo -e '\033[0;34mI will not manually configure my server\033[0m'

Run the package.

  % linecook run

The package can be run on any server accessible via ssh but runs locally (ie
on localhost) by default. See the generated 'config/ssh' file as well as the
documentation for {setting up a VM}[link:files/Tutorial/1%20-%20VM%20Setup.html].

== Installation

Linecook is available as a {gem}[http://rubygems.org/gems/linecook].

  % gem install linecook

